author: @ghalien52
text: I'm back after 4 years. I still remember the first time this was released, it was night if I remembered correctly. in the midst of my struggles in academics because of new normal resulted by covid 19, I was there at night, the modules being my sole company and I was sooooo drained. I still feel the heaviness I felt that night, and looking back makes me break down to tears. I was so depressed at a young age, over something that's not even deep and valid compared to others' struggles during the covid 19 pandemic. but this song contributed drastically to me. that night felt rather easy and comforting when I heard this song. all my worries were swept away and it was as if I was alone that time, living at a moment that feels surreal. hearing this song again after years was an avalanche of emotions---nostalgia, feeling of wanting to hurl, my insides twisting, my heart lightly beating, and feeling like that kid again. i just want to say that I'm beyond grateful for bts's music for you all have helped me through a lot, really. I'm in no way intentionally making this cringe, but I have no other way to express it any more than words. I want you all to keep producing music to your extent and keep helping people with it. you seven men means so much to me<333
